The argument was to this effect: It is not lawful for a Christian man in any religious aetion to deviate from the example of Christ and his Apostles ; But it is certain that Christ and his Apostles did not receive the bread and wine kneeling, but in another posture: Therefore we Christians ought to do the same.

17. We reply‚ first, that we have here the fallacy of a change of kind in the thing spoken of. The argument refers to Aetions 3 our controversy is about Postures. Granted that every action of Christ is to be imitated: but a Posture is not an action.

The two belong to different Praedicaments: (see Note Prael. 1. Art. 2.). Action is a Praedicament of itself t Posture belongs to the Praedicament Position. ⁷
